<br>
Slowley, Madmartigan creeped behind one of the stands on the street that was pediling foods. He reached out, and grabed some of the open goods, then started to flee, hoping that no one had caught him in the act. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/31/02 1:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A thief amidst</span><hr size=1> Poseidon appeared immediatly before Madmartigan in a haze of green light. The Gods strong arm whipped out and lashed out out at the thief in a clothesline aimed at his chest. The townsmen were oblivious to what had just happened but their patron God was well aware of all that had taken place. <br>
<br>
&quot;Not so fast buddy..&quot; shouted the Sea God as he sought to impede upon Madmartigan's escape. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/4/02 3:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lizazz.tripod.com/valmad6.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A thief amidst</span><hr size=1> Madmartigan didn't even see the god, untill he was lieing on the ground from the clothesline. Madmartigan, thinking that the person who just attacked him was just a person, he pulled out a dagger and stood, glaring at him. He looked up and down the man.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you want food, get your own. I stole this fair and square.&quot;<br>
<br>
Madmartigan took a bite of the food, and stood ready to move at a moments notice. <p>Madmartigan- Jokester, trickster, swordsmen, and madman.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/5/02 9:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A thief amidst</span><hr size=1> The dust rose about them from Madmartigan's fall in a thick cloud and the man's weapon flashed in the light. The god did not brace himself against any attack that might come his way, he had nothing to fear in any case since this man could never hope to beat him. Poseidon watched the man nibble at the food which then grew hard in Madmartigan's hands and crumpled in broken pieces to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;That was your problem thief, you stole it so now you won't be able to eat it. Now it is up to me to exact retribution for your crime for it was not lawful for you to do such a thing as you did, especially with my people.&quot;<br>
<br>
The god moved in closer to Madmartigan as a storm cloud which the man could have no hope of escaping. Skin shifted texture and became a thick grey hide and the God himself was changed into a rhino. Its cold black eyes glared at the man and a cold laugh ran from the rhino's lips.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your dead, dead man.&quot;<br>
<br>
After tensing its muscles the animal took off at Madmartigan with its sharp horn ready to gore the thief. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/7/02 3:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A thief amidst</span><hr size=1> ~Artemis appeared in a burst of green lights and shook her head. She pulled Mad out of way and stood befor ehim, looking to her uncle.~<br>
"I really do pity you Uncle, you have no cares for anyone but yourself. You were to kill because someone stole a loaf of bread to survive...How sad of you. No wonder Noone cares much for you, here on Earth, or up on Olympus. You are nothing but a bitter old coot."<br>
~She turned to Mad.~<br>
"Are you okay?" <p>~ The Silver Goddess~<br>
